40|$|Satellite {{emergency}} locator {{systems were}} studied. The {{objective of the}} study was to determine the feasibility and hardware requirements for satellite systems capable of identifying and locating the <b>position</b> <b>emergency</b> locator transmitters and <b>emergency</b> <b>position</b> indicating radio beacons. Both geosynchronous and near-polar-orbiting satellites were considered. One of the most important aspects {{of the study was}} to minimize the cost of the hardware required...|$|R
